# Multi-Product Architecture (Glassspider)

**Glassspider** is a product in the Laightworks hub-and-spoke ecosystem:

- Hub: `laightworks.com/login` and `laightworks.com/dashboard`
- Products: independent apps on `*.laightworks.com` (glassspider is one of them)
- No `portal.laightworks.com`
- No iframe integration unless explicitly approved

## Auth And Security

- All apps must validate Supabase sessions server-side.
- Dashboard visibility does not grant product access.
- Every product must independently check access before rendering protected UI or data.
- Shared auth must work across `.laightworks.com` cookies.
- Do not make shared auth changes without verifying the hub and at least one subdomain.
- Never expose service role keys in browser code or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables.

## Project Identity

- This repo is the **glassspider** product. Define `PROJECT_SLUG` as **`glassspider`** (or match `projects.slug` if the hub uses a different canonical slug—stay consistent with the database).
- Product access logic must use `PROJECT_SLUG`; do not hardcode one-off access checks in multiple places.
- Unauthenticated users redirect to `https://laightworks.com/login`.
- Authenticated users without access see access denied.

## Access Control

- Access is validated through shared tables such as `projects` and `project_access` (ecosystem convention—confirm names in the live schema before coding).
- Client-side-only access checks are prohibited.
- Frontend and user-triggered routes use the user's Supabase session with RLS.
- Trusted backend workers may use service role only server-side.

## Database (shared with Laightworks)

- Glassspider uses the **same Supabase/Postgres project** as the Laightworks site and sibling products.
- **Every table this product introduces for its own data MUST be prefixed with `glassspider_`** (example: `glassspider_items`, not `items`).
- Do not create glassspider-specific tables without the `glassspider_` prefix—they must not collide with Laightworks or other products.
- Shared ecosystem tables (e.g. auth, `projects`, `project_access`) stay as defined by the hub; do not rename them from this repo.
- Product rows should reference `project_id` (or the ecosystem’s canonical FK) when they belong to a registered project.

## Architecture Discipline

- Do not put major glassspider-only business logic into the hub/dashboard app; keep it in this repo.
- This app must remain independently deployable.
- Keep `/admin` for Laightworks owner operations and `/dashboard` for user-facing product launch (when applicable).
- When routes, auth, schema, or cross-product behavior changes, update `docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` and any existing ecosystem docs this repo maintains.
